clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Indicated for the treatment of opioid induced constipation OIC in adult patients with chronic non cancer pain

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Use of opioids induces slowing of gastrointestinal motility and transit Patients do not develop tolerance to these effects unlike many other opioid side effects Naloxegol antagonizes mu delta and kappa opioid receptors having the highest affinity for mu Antagonism of gastrointestinal mu opioid receptors by naloxegol inhibits opioid induced delay of gastrointestinal transit time
